1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,033
welcome back

2
00:00:01,033 --> 00:00:03,400
now that our journey is complete

3
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:06,400
I think we could have a nice recap of our adventure

4
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:10,600
our whole base is located in a single self sufficient dimension

5
00:00:10,766 --> 00:00:12,500
here there is no rain

6
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,466
no mob spawn

7
00:00:13,466 --> 00:00:15,066
and it's always day

8
00:00:15,266 --> 00:00:19,166
we received this place as a reward when we built our first rocket

9
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,266
and this is the main hall of the building

10
00:00:21,266 --> 00:00:22,900
in the middle of our base

11
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:24,200
here we have a screen

12
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:26,833
that will show us the charge of our main battery

13
00:00:26,966 --> 00:00:30,600
some monitor terminals to keep an eye on the amount of fuel

14
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:32,800
and some for the endgame stuff

15
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,200
talking about storage and craftings

16
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,466
our main ae2 controller is right above us

17
00:00:38,466 --> 00:00:41,366
to manage all of its channels in an easier way

18
00:00:41,366 --> 00:00:44,500
we used a tight mix of peer to peer and wireless connectors

19
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:48,000
to get all of the controller facades on a nice wall

20
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:51,400
we can see all of the channels with our network visualizer

21
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,633
but that doesn't really help us that much while working in that location

22
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:59,066
here we also have all of our crafting CPUs

23
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,666
we have different sizes

24
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:05,833
but the biggest ones are those towers equipped with singularity crafting storages

25
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:09,900
those can hold crafting orders up to 8 exabytes

26
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:12,633
while we will never get close to that amount

27
00:01:12,633 --> 00:01:14,800
they are helpful when doing huge orders

28
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:18,433
that would otherwise need too big conventional CPUs

29
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:23,033
all of those CPUs are also doing some crafting self started

30
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:26,200
those are not from crafting cards or level emitters

31
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:28,066
but from level maintainers

32
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:31,533
with those it is easy to keep a stock of what we want

33
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:35,700
and when needed, request a craft with a specific batch size

34
00:01:35,766 --> 00:01:38,900
next to that we have our main generic storage

35
00:01:38,966 --> 00:01:41,466
and to manage all of those items

36
00:01:41,466 --> 00:01:45,400
we ended up using the artificial universe storage cells

37
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:48,100
but this is just our main ae2 system

38
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:50,966
which mostly manages on demand craftings

39
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:55,533
the patterns for the stuff we use in huge amounts have all been multiplied a lot

40
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:58,433
and instead of using interfaces

41
00:01:58,433 --> 00:02:03,466
we input materials directly inside the machines with the embedded crafting buffers

42
00:02:03,466 --> 00:02:08,100
those are blocks that can be used when building the mid to late game multi blocks

43
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:12,166
and when we craft huge amounts of early game materials

44
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:15,366
we can see that the main limitation is integer 32

45
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:19,366
and that we can process those amounts of items in a single tick

46
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:25,033
also you can now guess how we ended up needing 8 exabyte storage crafting units

47
00:02:25,033 --> 00:02:27,466
this was our main ae2 network

48
00:02:27,466 --> 00:02:29,166
but not the only one

49
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:33,400
we have countless sub networks for all kinds of purposes

50
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:36,200
such as assembly lines of all kinds

51
00:02:36,366 --> 00:02:39,500
but we also have another huge and spread network

52
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,633
the mass produced storage one

53
00:02:41,766 --> 00:02:47,033
this one will manage all of the resources produced and processed in unlimited amounts

54
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,433
and it still uses digital singularity cells

55
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:54,200
most of our raw resources come from this eye of harmony

56
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,966
with its 211 astral array fabricators

57
00:02:57,966 --> 00:03:01,466
it works with a 16000 parallel multiplier

58
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:04,500
and it will produce about anything we could need

59
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:07,233
the biggest exception is probably a orundum

60
00:03:07,433 --> 00:03:09,233
this material is a weird thing

61
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:12,300
that could be produced by fusing together two plates

62
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:15,233
but we are getting it as an ore from a space elevator

63
00:03:15,366 --> 00:03:16,700
from a space elevator

64
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:20,866
we are also pumping all kinds of fluids which we could need

65
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:24,400
also we still have some void miners in the deep dark

66
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:28,466
just to integrate with any possible ore that can be seen in NEI

67
00:03:28,766 --> 00:03:32,666
the ones we care about are processed in integrated ore facilities

68
00:03:32,666 --> 00:03:36,100
while the rest is stocked up in yet another subnetwork

69
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,266
to power all of that stuff

70
00:03:38,266 --> 00:03:42,066
 we are using the shielded Lagrangian annihilation matrix

71
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,066
to fuel it

72
00:03:43,066 --> 00:03:44,500
we use antimatter

73
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,466
five millions at a time

74
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:52,500
which will output energy in bursts of almost integer 64 energy units at a time

75
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,766
we store that energy in a wireless energy network

76
00:03:55,766 --> 00:03:58,033
which has a really huge capacity

77
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:02,066
our generator to run uses antimatter as fuel

78
00:04:02,266 --> 00:04:03,900
to produce such fuel

79
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:08,400
we use 24 semi stable antimatter stabilization sequencers

80
00:04:08,566 --> 00:04:12,233
and this is a multi block with some peculiar requirements

81
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,366
the most important thing to know is that it needs the same amount of antimatter in each hatch

82
00:04:17,366 --> 00:04:21,033
and that it will keep randomly changing the value in its hatches

83
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,633
to keep it under check

84
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:25,233
we use SFM and a bunch of covers

85
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:29,466
and the production will also use some quite expensive materials

86
00:04:29,466 --> 00:04:32,166
to make a decent amount of antimatter

87
00:04:32,166 --> 00:04:33,866
to boost the production

88
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:38,366
we also had to make a dedicated naquadah fuel production facility

89
00:04:38,366 --> 00:04:44,033
all done with AE2 hatches and sub networks to reach high enough crafting speeds

90
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:45,966
for power generation

91
00:04:45,966 --> 00:04:48,833
we also have 100 Dyson Spheres

92
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:50,466
but those are no longer loaded

93
00:04:50,466 --> 00:04:52,966
since the power production is negligible

94
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:54,966
and now we can step outside

95
00:04:54,966 --> 00:04:57,500
and start having a look at the machines in our base

96
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:01,000
starting from the light bulb on top of our main building

97
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:02,700
the forge of the gods

98
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:07,266
that huge thing is used to work materials at high temperatures

99
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:10,600
the main structure can host 4 different modules

100
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,033
that can do different kind of tasks

101
00:05:13,066 --> 00:05:15,800
the first one is just a better blast furnace

102
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,800
the second one acts more like a blast smelter

103
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,600
melting materials down to liquid form

104
00:05:21,666 --> 00:05:25,566
the real advantage here is that we no longer need vacuum freezer

105
00:05:25,766 --> 00:05:29,033
the third module can turn any element into plasma

106
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:31,966
this will offer alternatives to fusion recipes

107
00:05:31,966 --> 00:05:34,666
and often reduce the amount of needed steps

108
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:38,800
and we can also use it to make plasmas that fusion can't make

109
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,800
the last module can only make two recipes

110
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,200
magmatter and quark gluon

111
00:05:44,233 --> 00:05:48,633
and the reason NEI looks weird on those two crafting recipes is because

112
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:51,633
this is a really particular processing mechanic

113
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:53,000
to make magmatter

114
00:05:53,066 --> 00:05:55,900
machine will start by giving us 2 fluids

115
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,900
we have to calculate the difference

116
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,066
multiply it by 144

117
00:05:59,066 --> 00:06:05,600
and give it back as plasma of the material of a tiny dust the machine also gave us

118
00:06:05,766 --> 00:06:07,100
for the quark gluon

119
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,100
we start with some random elements

120
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:14,066
and we have to send back plasma equivalent to 9 times what the machine gave us

121
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:19,233
the working speed and efficiency of all of those modules can scale up with the upgrades

122
00:06:19,233 --> 00:06:23,700
that we can unlock in a skill tree inside the main controller of the structure

123
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,666
those skills are unlocked by using Graviton Shards

124
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:32,433
points that are earned by reaching milestones in the usage of the machine

125
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:37,066
and this is not the only place where we have to face automation minigames

126
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:40,566
the other complex tasks are given by the waterline

127
00:06:41,066 --> 00:06:44,400
here we have an 8 step process for filtering water

128
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:47,366
but let's see those steps one at a time

129
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:49,600
the first step is a clarifier

130
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:54,800
which will simply use filters to remove the big particles suspended in our dirty water

131
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,300
the second step is ozonation

132
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,433
we inject some ozone in the water

133
00:06:59,433 --> 00:07:02,766
to take out some of the contaminants that react with it

134
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:06,366
the only challenge here is to pick the right size of input hatch

135
00:07:06,366 --> 00:07:07,900
and keep it filled up

136
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:10,366
the next step is flocculation

137
00:07:10,366 --> 00:07:13,433
which consists of adding some flocculant to aggregate

138
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,000
and then collect suspended particulates

139
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,700
and here things starts to get interesting

140
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:23,666
because we have to insert the flocculant in perfect multiplies for it to work properly

141
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,600
but it's not too hard

142
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:29,600
we can ensure the insertion of a perfect amount with a bunch of covers

143
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:35,266
next we have to correct the acidity of our water in a pH neutralization plant

144
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:40,200
here we will be adding some alkaline or acid stuff to correct the pH

145
00:07:40,366 --> 00:07:41,800
to automate that process

146
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,066
we can use the embedded pH sensors

147
00:07:44,066 --> 00:07:46,666
and some basic Redstone control

148
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,700
once we neutralize the pH of our water

149
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,766
we have to do some Thermal cycles

150
00:07:51,766 --> 00:07:54,800
to ensure no weird stuff is left inside it

151
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:59,200
to do so, we blast it with helium plasma above the temperature of the sun

152
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,700
and then cool it down to absolute 0

153
00:08:02,366 --> 00:08:05,800
here, to keep the temperature in check we use SFM

154
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:09,566
with an external dummy item to keep track of the heat cycles

155
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:12,000
that will leave some ions in the water

156
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,233
so

157
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:15,400
we have to use laser to shoot those out of our water

158
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,833
but we have to do that with different lenses

159
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:20,500
in the correct order and with the correct timing

160
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:21,100
luckily

161
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,800
we have a sensor that will make swaps easy

162
00:08:24,066 --> 00:08:26,833
next we have the decontaminant degasser unit

163
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,800
which will have random made up issues

164
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,100
just to add an extra challenge

165
00:08:31,266 --> 00:08:34,200
this machine can't express its feelings properly

166
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:37,700
the best it can do is try to communicate with us in binary

167
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:41,366
so we hired another SFM controller to talk with her

168
00:08:41,466 --> 00:08:42,233
finally

169
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:46,200
we have the Absolute Baryonic Perfection Purification unit

170
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:51,700
that machine will fix every subatomic particle out of position contained in our water

171
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:53,266
to automate this

172
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:54,366
we have built a setup

173
00:08:54,366 --> 00:08:58,966
that will first prepare some quark releasing catalysts in a specific order

174
00:08:58,966 --> 00:09:02,833
and then one by one insert those inside the machine

175
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,900
but our Redstone and automation challenges aren't done yet

176
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:10,033
we also had to manage black holes

177
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:13,000
this machine is mostly a powerful compressor

178
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:17,833
but there are some recipes that require a strength that only a black hole can achieve

179
00:09:17,966 --> 00:09:19,700
to make this machine work

180
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,800
we first have to open a black hole inside it with a black hole seed

181
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:27,066
however this black hole will slowly shrink

182
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,066
becoming less and less stable

183
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,800
to halt that process

184
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,433
we can add some space time to the machine

185
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:37,066
but the cost of space time will keep increasing exponentially

186
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,966
and when the black hole is at its most unstable phase

187
00:09:40,966 --> 00:09:44,833
it will manage to compress four times as many items at once

188
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:48,233
and when the upkeep cost becomes too high

189
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:50,766
we can close the black hole with a collapsar

190
00:09:51,233 --> 00:09:54,633
to properly manage all the different recipes we are going to do

191
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:56,866
and the correct insertion of the items

192
00:09:56,866 --> 00:09:59,666
we have designed a proper Redstone circuit

193
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:03,700
we have 2 different ones with different timer settings

194
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:06,900
and we also have two extra black hole compressors

195
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,866
to passively make eternal singularities

196
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:13,033
next we can check out the assembly lines

197
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:16,500
the oldest 14 are for generic craftings

198
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:20,166
here we do all the recipes we need in small amounts

199
00:10:20,466 --> 00:10:27,066
the data sticks with the unlocked recipes are kept in chained data banks that are connected by optical fibers

200
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:30,500
and here we have a collection of stuff we almost never craft

201
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:34,200
and thus got removed even from this set of assembly lines

202
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,466
on the contrary

203
00:10:35,466 --> 00:10:38,300
stuff we need often but is really hard to craft

204
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:41,266
is made in the nearby advanced assembly lines

205
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,233
here we use way more energy

206
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:46,366
and we craft small batches of expensive stuff

207
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:48,500
and even with all of those overclocks

208
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:52,566
it still takes a while to craft those time intense parts

209
00:10:52,766 --> 00:10:55,866
to manage the parallelization of the assembly line

210
00:10:55,866 --> 00:10:59,033
we have a slightly more complex item feeding system

211
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:03,300
which has an AE2 subnetwork for each slice of each assembly line

212
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,433
overclocking isn't efficient

213
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:08,266
so for stuff that doesn't take as much time

214
00:11:08,266 --> 00:11:09,800
and we need in bigger amounts

215
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,466
we have a different setup

216
00:11:11,766 --> 00:11:14,400
we have 8 lines of 8 assembly lines

217
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:17,200
with each line sharing the same inputs

218
00:11:17,366 --> 00:11:21,600
and those are almost always constantly crafting lots of things

219
00:11:21,866 --> 00:11:24,900
but there was one thing which we needed in way bigger amounts

220
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:27,500
that this setup wouldn't keep up with

221
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,100
circuits

222
00:11:28,266 --> 00:11:28,800
for those

223
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:32,633
we made 88 assembly lines sharing the same inputs

224
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:35,066
but even that still wasn't enough

225
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:39,200
the storage for our queued up craftings were constantly full

226
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,666
so we started making extra building

227
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:43,633
dedicated to each circuit

228
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:47,300
the next thing that caused some inventory management issues

229
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:50,666
were our dimensionally transcendent plasma forges

230
00:11:50,866 --> 00:11:52,600
we have 60 of those

231
00:11:52,866 --> 00:11:55,700
36 of those are working on demand crafting

232
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:59,200
provided by the crafting buffer Linked In our base

233
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:03,433
the other 24 are passively doing stuff using the convergence module

234
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:06,266
which otherwise we wouldn't be able to keep up with

235
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:06,866
finally

236
00:12:06,866 --> 00:12:10,066
there are many machines we had to build in huge amounts

237
00:12:10,066 --> 00:12:12,566
to keep up with the processing demands

238
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:16,833
most of those don't have any particularly hard mechanic to showcase

239
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:19,900
so I think we can just fly around and have a look

240
00:12:52,966 --> 00:12:54,900
if you want to have a look by yourself

241
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:56,800
and inspect anything you want

242
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,866
you can download the save in the video description

243
00:13:00,566 --> 00:13:01,600
next to the spawn

244
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,366
you should be able to find a chest

245
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:05,066
with all of my equipment

246
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,800
if you want the mini map to be complete

247
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:11,000
I also included journey map files

248
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,600
once you are ready

249
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:16,100
you can use the relocator to relocate to the base

250
00:13:16,266 --> 00:13:17,033
now

251
00:13:17,033 --> 00:13:18,466
before you do anything

252
00:13:18,466 --> 00:13:21,266
there are a couple of things you should know and check

253
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:24,833
the Wireless Energy battery is linked to a player

254
00:13:25,266 --> 00:13:28,066
I don't know how it works in single player

255
00:13:28,066 --> 00:13:35,900
but I assume you'd still have to join my network if you wanted to use Wireless Energy for any modification you could want to try

256
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:38,600
if the Questbook command doesn't work

257
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:42,300
you can just rebuild the controller of the main power generator

258
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,866
just make sure it now has your name

259
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:46,700
and to turn on wireless mode

260
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:51,000
one other thing you might won't be able to use is ae2

261
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:52,033
in that case

262
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:54,033
rebuild the security terminal

263
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:56,400
and then relink the wireless terminal

264
00:13:56,866 --> 00:13:57,233
next

265
00:13:57,233 --> 00:14:00,300
sometimes while loading backups

266
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,500
the waterline could stop working

267
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:03,666
in that case

268
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:05,766
just turn on the main controller

269
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:09,766
other times the forge automations will get stuck

270
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:11,266
if that is the case

271
00:14:11,266 --> 00:14:13,700
remove the fluids from the afflicted setup

272
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,366
and reset the mini game

273
00:14:15,766 --> 00:14:17,300
this rarely happens

274
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:21,166
so make sure it is stuck before being the cause of the issue

275
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,500
I probably forgot other things

276
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,600
just ask in the comments

277
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:26,633
bye bye

278
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:01,033
欢迎回来

279
00:00:01,033 --> 00:00:03,400
我们的旅程已经结束

280
00:00:03,400 --> 00:00:06,400
我想我们可以好好总结一下这次冒险

281
00:00:06,400 --> 00:00:10,600
我们的整个基地位于一个自给自足的维度

282
00:00:10,766 --> 00:00:12,500
这里没有雨

283
00:00:12,500 --> 00:00:13,466
怪物不会生成

284
00:00:13,466 --> 00:00:15,066
永远是白天

285
00:00:15,266 --> 00:00:19,166

我们在造出第一枚火箭时得到了这个私人维度奖励


286
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:21,266
这里是大楼的主厅

287
00:00:21,266 --> 00:00:22,900
位于基地的中间

288
00:00:22,900 --> 00:00:24,200
这有一个屏幕

289
00:00:24,200 --> 00:00:26,833
它会展示主电池的电量

290
00:00:26,966 --> 00:00:30,600
有一些终端用于监视燃料的数量

291
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:32,800
以及一些大后期材料

292
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:35,200

至于存储和自动合成的设备


293
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:38,466
我们的主AE控制器位于上方

294
00:00:38,466 --> 00:00:41,366

为了以更简单的方式管理频道


295
00:00:41,366 --> 00:00:44,500
我们使用了p2p和无线连接器的紧密组合

296
00:00:44,500 --> 00:00:48,000
把所有控制器都映射到一堵漂亮的墙上

297
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:51,400
我们可以使用网络可视化工具查看所有频道

298
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:55,633

但它对我们在这里工作用处不大


299
00:00:55,666 --> 00:00:59,066
这里还有所有的合成CPU

300
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,666
我们有不同尺寸的

301
00:01:00,666 --> 00:01:05,833
但最大的是那些配备了奇点合成存储器的

302
00:01:05,900 --> 00:01:09,900
这些可以容纳高达8EB的订单

303
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:12,633
虽然我们永远不会接近那个数量

304
00:01:12,633 --> 00:01:14,800
但它们在下大订单时很有帮助

305
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:18,433
否则将需要太大的传统CPU

306
00:01:18,633 --> 00:01:23,033
所有这些CPU也在做一些自动发起的订单

307
00:01:23,233 --> 00:01:26,200
这些不是来自合成卡或发信器

308
00:01:26,200 --> 00:01:28,066
而是来自库存维持器

309
00:01:28,166 --> 00:01:31,533
这些能很容易维持我们想要的库存数量

310
00:01:31,533 --> 00:01:35,700
当有需要时，它会发起具有特定大小的订单

311
00:01:35,766 --> 00:01:38,900
接下来是我们的主要通用存储

312
00:01:38,966 --> 00:01:41,466
为了管理所有的东西

313
00:01:41,466 --> 00:01:45,400
我们最终使用了人造宇宙存储单元

314
00:01:45,433 --> 00:01:48,100
但这只是我们的主网

315
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:50,966
主要用于一些按需制作

316
00:01:51,033 --> 00:01:55,533
我们大量使用的东西的样板倍增了好几次

317
00:01:55,533 --> 00:01:58,433
不同于使用ME接口

318
00:01:58,433 --> 00:02:03,466
我们直接用有带缓存的样板总成向机器内输入材料

319
00:02:03,466 --> 00:02:08,100
这些是在中后期多方块机器中使用的方块

320
00:02:08,200 --> 00:02:12,166
当我们制作大量早期游戏材料时

321
00:02:12,166 --> 00:02:15,366
我们可以看到主要限制是int32

322
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:19,366
我们可以在一个游戏刻内处理这些数量的物品

323
00:02:19,500 --> 00:02:25,033
你现在应该可以猜到为什么要8EB的存储制作单元

324
00:02:25,033 --> 00:02:27,466
这是我们的主网

325
00:02:27,466 --> 00:02:29,166
但不是唯一的一个

326
00:02:29,300 --> 00:02:33,400
我们有无数各种用途的子网

327
00:02:33,400 --> 00:02:36,200
比如各种装配线

328
00:02:36,366 --> 00:02:39,500
但我们还有另一个庞大而分散的网络

329
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:41,633
用于存储批量生产的物品

330
00:02:41,766 --> 00:02:47,033
它将管理无限量生产和加工的所有资源

331
00:02:47,100 --> 00:02:50,433
它仍然使用数字奇点单元

332
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:54,200
我们大部分的原始资源来自鸿蒙之眼

333
00:02:54,400 --> 00:02:57,966
EoH中塞了211个星阵

334
00:02:57,966 --> 00:03:01,466
也就是16000倍并行

335
00:03:01,666 --> 00:03:04,500
它会生产出我们需要的任何东西

336
00:03:04,700 --> 00:03:07,233

最大的例外可能是合成玉


337
00:03:07,433 --> 00:03:09,233
这是一种奇怪的材料

338
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:12,300
可以通过将两个板压缩在一起产生

339
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:15,233
但我们是从太空电梯里获取它的矿石的

340
00:03:15,366 --> 00:03:16,700
从太空电梯里

341
00:03:16,700 --> 00:03:20,866
我们还抽取了可能需要的各种液体

342
00:03:21,100 --> 00:03:24,400
另外，我们还有一些位于漆黑世界的虚空采矿厂

343
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:28,466
为了补充任何可能在NEI中看到的矿物

344
00:03:28,766 --> 00:03:32,666
我们关心的矿物在集成矿石处理厂中加工

345
00:03:32,666 --> 00:03:36,100
其余的储存在另一个子网中

346
00:03:36,500 --> 00:03:38,266
为所有这些东西供电

347
00:03:38,266 --> 00:03:42,066
 我们用的是屏蔽拉格朗日湮灭矩阵

348
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,066
为了给它供给燃料

349
00:03:43,066 --> 00:03:44,500
我们使用反物质

350
00:03:44,500 --> 00:03:46,466
一次五百万升

351
00:03:46,633 --> 00:03:52,500
它将一次输出接近2^63 EU

352
00:03:52,700 --> 00:03:55,766
我们将能量存储在无线电网中

353
00:03:55,766 --> 00:03:58,033
它的容量非常大

354
00:03:58,233 --> 00:04:02,066
我们的发电机使用反物质作为燃料

355
00:04:02,266 --> 00:04:03,900
要生产这种燃料

356
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:08,400
我们使用24个半稳定反物质稳定序列器

357
00:04:08,566 --> 00:04:12,233
这是一个有一些特殊要求的多方块

358
00:04:12,500 --> 00:04:17,366
最重要的是每个仓室需要有等量的反物质

359
00:04:17,366 --> 00:04:21,033
它会不断随机改变仓室中的反物质数量

360
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:22,633
为了保持数量一致

361
00:04:22,633 --> 00:04:25,233
我们使用SFM和一堆覆盖板

362
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:29,466
发电过程也会使用一些相当昂贵的材料

363
00:04:29,466 --> 00:04:32,166
制造大量的反物质

364
00:04:32,166 --> 00:04:33,866
为了提高产量

365
00:04:33,866 --> 00:04:38,366
我们还必须建造一个专门的硅岩燃料生产设施

366
00:04:38,366 --> 00:04:41,866
所有这些都是通过AE仓室和子网完成的

367
00:04:41,866 --> 00:04:44,033
以达到足够高的制造速度

368
00:04:44,433 --> 00:04:45,966
对于发电

369
00:04:45,966 --> 00:04:48,833
我们还有100个戴森球

370
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:50,466
但那些区块不再加载了

371
00:04:50,466 --> 00:04:52,966
因为它们产出的电力微不足道

372
00:04:53,166 --> 00:04:54,966
现在我们可以出去

373
00:04:54,966 --> 00:04:57,500
看看我们基地里的机器

374
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:01,000
从我们主楼顶上的灯泡开始

375
00:05:01,033 --> 00:05:02,700
也就是诸神之锻炉

376
00:05:02,833 --> 00:05:07,266
那个巨大的东西是用来在高温下处理材料的

377
00:05:07,400 --> 00:05:10,600
主体结构可以承载4个不同的模块

378
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:13,033
用于处理不同类型的任务

379
00:05:13,066 --> 00:05:15,800
第一个只是一个更好的高炉

380
00:05:15,800 --> 00:05:18,800
第二个更像是熔液高炉

381
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:21,600
能够将材料熔化成液态

382
00:05:21,666 --> 00:05:25,566
真正的优势是我们不再需要真空冷冻

383
00:05:25,766 --> 00:05:29,033
第三个模块可以将任何元素转化为等离子体

384
00:05:29,233 --> 00:05:31,966
这将提供聚变配方的替代

385
00:05:31,966 --> 00:05:34,666
并经常减少所需步骤的数量

386
00:05:34,666 --> 00:05:38,800
我们也可以用它制造无法聚变的等离子体

387
00:05:38,900 --> 00:05:41,800
最后一个模块只能做两个配方

388
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:44,200
磁物质和夸克胶子等离子体

389
00:05:44,233 --> 00:05:48,633
在NEI的这两个上看起来很奇怪的原因是因为

390
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:51,633
它拥有一种非常特殊的加工机制

391
00:05:51,733 --> 00:05:53,000
要制造磁物质

392
00:05:53,066 --> 00:05:55,900
机器将从给我们两种液体开始

393
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,900

我们必须计算它们的差


394
00:05:57,900 --> 00:05:59,066
乘以144

395
00:05:59,066 --> 00:06:05,600
把机器给我们的小搓粉对应的等离子体输入回机器

396
00:06:05,766 --> 00:06:07,100
对于夸克胶子等离子体

397
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:09,100
我们从一些随机元素开始

398
00:06:09,100 --> 00:06:14,066
我们必须送回机器给我们的9倍的等离子体

399
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:19,233
所有这些模块的工作速度和效率都可以随着升级而提高

400
00:06:19,233 --> 00:06:23,700
我们可以在结构的主方块内的技能树中解锁它们

401
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:27,666
这些技能通过使用引力子碎片解锁

402
00:06:27,666 --> 00:06:32,433
那是通过达到机器使用里程碑而获得的积分

403
00:06:32,666 --> 00:06:37,066
这不是我们唯一要面对的自动化小游戏

404
00:06:37,233 --> 00:06:40,566

其他复杂的任务来自净化水线


405
00:06:41,066 --> 00:06:44,400
这里我们有一个过滤水的8步过程

406
00:06:44,500 --> 00:06:47,366
让我们一步步来看

407
00:06:47,566 --> 00:06:49,600
第一步是澄清

408
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:54,800
它将简单地使用过滤器来去除悬浮在脏水中的大颗粒

409
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:57,300
第二步是臭氧化

410
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,433
我们在水中注入一些臭氧

411
00:06:59,433 --> 00:07:02,766
去除一些与之反应的污染物

412
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:06,366
这里唯一的挑战是选择合适尺寸的输入仓

413
00:07:06,366 --> 00:07:07,900
并保持它充满

414
00:07:08,166 --> 00:07:10,366
下一步是絮凝

415
00:07:10,366 --> 00:07:13,433
它包括添加一些絮凝剂用于絮凝

416
00:07:13,433 --> 00:07:16,000
然后收集悬浮微粒

417
00:07:16,000 --> 00:07:18,700
现在事情开始变得有趣起来

418
00:07:18,700 --> 00:07:23,666
因为我们必须以完美的倍数输入絮凝剂才能正常工作

419
00:07:23,833 --> 00:07:25,600
但这并不太难

420
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:29,600
我们可以用一堆覆盖板确保输入完美的数量

421
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:35,266
接下来，我们在pH中和装置中校正水的酸度

422
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:40,200
在这里，我们将添加一些碱性或酸性的东西来校正pH值

423
00:07:40,366 --> 00:07:41,800
要自动化该过程

424
00:07:41,800 --> 00:07:44,066
我们可以使用嵌入式pH传感器

425
00:07:44,066 --> 00:07:46,666
和一些基本的红石电路

426
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:49,700
一旦我们中和了水的酸碱度

427
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:51,766
我们必须做一些热循环

428
00:07:51,766 --> 00:07:54,800
以确保水里没有奇怪的东西

429
00:07:54,900 --> 00:07:59,200
为此，我们用高于太阳温度的氦等离子体加热它

430
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:01,700
然后将其冷却到绝对零度

431
00:08:02,366 --> 00:08:05,800
在这里，为了控制温度，我们使用SFM

432
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:09,566
使用外部虚拟物品以跟踪热量循环

433
00:08:09,666 --> 00:08:12,000
这会在水中留下一些离子

434
00:08:12,000 --> 00:08:12,233
所以

435
00:08:12,233 --> 00:08:15,400
我们必须用激光把它们从水里射出来

436
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,833
但是我们必须用不同的棱镜来做

437
00:08:17,833 --> 00:08:20,500
同时要保证正确的顺序和时间

438
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:21,100
幸运的是

439
00:08:21,100 --> 00:08:23,800
我们有一个传感器可以让交换变得轻松

440
00:08:24,066 --> 00:08:26,833
接下来是净化脱气装置

441
00:08:26,833 --> 00:08:28,800
这将有随机编造的问题

442
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,100
只是为了增加一个额外的挑战

443
00:08:31,266 --> 00:08:34,200
这台机器不能正确地表达它的感情

444
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:37,700
它最多只能用二进制和我们交流

445
00:08:37,833 --> 00:08:41,366
所以我们雇了另一个SFM管理员和她谈谈

446
00:08:41,466 --> 00:08:42,233
最后

447
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:46,200
是绝对重子完美净化单元

448
00:08:46,400 --> 00:08:51,700
那台机器会修复水里每一个处于错误位置的亚原子粒子

449
00:08:52,033 --> 00:08:53,266
要自动化这个过程

450
00:08:53,266 --> 00:08:54,366
我们搭好一个装置

451
00:08:54,366 --> 00:08:58,966
首先按照特定顺序准备一些夸克释放催化剂

452
00:08:58,966 --> 00:09:02,833
然后一个接一个地将它们输入机器

453
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:06,900
但是我们的红石和自动化挑战还没有结束

454
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:10,033
我们还必须管理黑洞

455
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:13,000
这台机器主要是一台强大的压缩机

456
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:17,833
但是有些配方需要只有黑洞才能达到的强度

457
00:09:17,966 --> 00:09:19,700
为了让这台机器工作

458
00:09:19,700 --> 00:09:23,800
我们首先得用黑洞种子在里面打开一个黑洞

459
00:09:24,166 --> 00:09:27,066
然而这个黑洞会慢慢缩小

460
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:29,066
变得越来越不稳定

461
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:30,800
要停止这个过程

462
00:09:30,800 --> 00:09:33,433
我们可以给机器增加一些时空

463
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:37,066
但时空成本将呈指数增长

464
00:09:37,333 --> 00:09:40,966
当黑洞处于最不稳定的阶段时

465
00:09:40,966 --> 00:09:44,833
它将一次压缩四倍多的物品

466
00:09:45,033 --> 00:09:48,233
当维护成本过高时

467
00:09:48,233 --> 00:09:50,766
我们可以用黑洞坍塌器关闭黑洞

468
00:09:51,233 --> 00:09:54,633
为了正确管理我们要做的所有不同配方

469
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:56,866
以及正确输入物品

470
00:09:56,866 --> 00:09:59,666
我们设计了一个合适的红石电路

471
00:09:59,833 --> 00:10:03,700
我们有两套不同的定时器设置

472
00:10:04,033 --> 00:10:06,900
还有两个额外的黑洞压缩机

473
00:10:06,900 --> 00:10:09,866
用于被动制造永恒奇点

474
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:13,033
接下来我们可以去看看装配线

475
00:10:13,100 --> 00:10:16,500
最老的14个用于通用配方

476
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:20,166

我们在这些装配线上运行只有少量需求的配方


477
00:10:20,466 --> 00:10:27,066
具有解锁配方的闪存保存在通过光纤串联的数据库中

478
00:10:27,233 --> 00:10:30,500
这里我们收集了一些几乎从未制作过的东西

479
00:10:30,500 --> 00:10:34,200
因此从这组装配线上被移除了

480
00:10:34,300 --> 00:10:35,466
另一方面

481
00:10:35,466 --> 00:10:38,300
我们经常需要但很难制作的东西

482
00:10:38,300 --> 00:10:41,266
是在附近的进阶装配线上制造的

483
00:10:41,400 --> 00:10:43,233
在这里我们使用更多的能量

484
00:10:43,233 --> 00:10:46,366
我们小批量制作昂贵的东西

485
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:48,500
即使有这么多超频

486
00:10:48,500 --> 00:10:52,566

制作那些耗时长的部件仍然需要一段时间


487
00:10:52,766 --> 00:10:55,866
为了实现装配线的并行

488
00:10:55,866 --> 00:10:59,033
我们有一个稍微复杂一点的物品供给系统

489
00:10:59,033 --> 00:11:03,300
每个装配线的每个切片都有一个子网

490
00:11:03,600 --> 00:11:05,433
超频效率不高

491
00:11:05,433 --> 00:11:08,266
所以对于不需要太多时间

492
00:11:08,266 --> 00:11:09,800
同时需要更大数量的

493
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,466
我们有不同的设置

494
00:11:11,766 --> 00:11:14,400
我们有8*8条装配线

495
00:11:14,400 --> 00:11:17,200
每一行共享相同的输入

496
00:11:17,366 --> 00:11:21,600
这些几乎总是在不断地制作很多东西

497
00:11:21,866 --> 00:11:24,900
但是有一样东西我们需要更多

498
00:11:24,900 --> 00:11:27,500
而这个设置的速度跟不上

499
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:28,100
就是电路板

500
00:11:28,266 --> 00:11:28,800
对于那些

501
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:32,633
我们建造了共享相同的输入的88条装配线

502
00:11:32,833 --> 00:11:35,066
但这还不够

503
00:11:35,200 --> 00:11:39,200
用于缓存原料的储存总是爆满

504
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:41,666
所以我们开始建造额外的建筑

505
00:11:41,666 --> 00:11:43,633
用于制造各类电路

506
00:11:43,900 --> 00:11:47,300
下一个导致一些库存管理问题的东西

507
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:50,666
是超维度等离子锻炉

508
00:11:50,866 --> 00:11:52,600
我们有60个锻炉

509
00:11:52,866 --> 00:11:55,700
其中36个按需制作

510
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:59,200
由连接到基地的输入总成提供原材料

511
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:03,433
其他24个正在使用超维校准矩阵进行被动生产

512
00:12:03,433 --> 00:12:06,266
否则我们跟不上需求

513
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:06,866
最后

514
00:12:06,866 --> 00:12:10,066
我们必须大量制造许多机器

515
00:12:10,066 --> 00:12:12,566
来满足材料处理需求

516
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:16,833
大多数都没有什么特别难的机制可以展示

517
00:12:16,833 --> 00:12:19,900
所以我想我们可以飞过去看看

518
00:12:52,966 --> 00:12:54,900
如果你想自己看看

519
00:12:54,900 --> 00:12:56,800
并检查任何想要的东西

520
00:12:56,800 --> 00:12:59,866
你可以下载简介里的存档

521
00:13:00,566 --> 00:13:01,600
在出生点旁边

522
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,366
你应该能找到一个箱子

523
00:13:03,366 --> 00:13:05,066
里面有我所有的装备

524
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,800
如果你想要完整的地图

525
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:11,000
我还在压缩包里加入地图文件

526
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:12,600
一旦你准备好了

527
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:16,100
你可以使用定位器传送到基地

528
00:13:16,266 --> 00:13:17,033
现在

529
00:13:17,033 --> 00:13:18,466
在你做任何事情之前

530
00:13:18,466 --> 00:13:21,266
有几件事你应该知道并检查

531
00:13:21,666 --> 00:13:24,833
无线电网与玩家绑定

532
00:13:25,266 --> 00:13:28,066
我不知道单人模式该怎么处理

533
00:13:28,066 --> 00:13:32,433
但我假设如果你想使用无线电网

534
00:13:32,433 --> 00:13:35,900
你仍然需要加入我的网络

535
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:38,600
如果任务书提到的命令不起作用

536
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:42,300
你可以重建主发电机的控制器

537
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,866
只要确保它现在有你的名字

538
00:13:44,866 --> 00:13:46,700
并打开无线模式

539
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:51,000
你可能无法使用的另一个东西是AE

540
00:13:51,233 --> 00:13:52,033
那样的话

541
00:13:52,033 --> 00:13:54,033
重建安全终端

542
00:13:54,033 --> 00:13:56,400
然后重新连接无线终端

543
00:13:56,866 --> 00:13:57,233
下一个

544
00:13:57,233 --> 00:14:00,300
有时在加载备份时

545
00:14:00,300 --> 00:14:02,500
净化水线可能会停止工作

546
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:03,666
那样的话

547
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:05,766
只需打开主控制器

548
00:14:06,200 --> 00:14:09,766
有的时候神锻自动化会卡住

549
00:14:09,900 --> 00:14:11,266
如果是这样的话

550
00:14:11,266 --> 00:14:13,700

清除受影响的装置中的液体


551
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,366

并重置小游戏


552
00:14:15,766 --> 00:14:17,300
这种情况很少发生

553
00:14:17,300 --> 00:14:18,866
所以要确保它卡住了

554
00:14:18,866 --> 00:14:21,166
否则你可能变成它卡住的原因

555
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,500
我可能忘了其他事

556
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,600
就在评论里问问

557
00:14:25,666 --> 00:14:26,633
拜拜

558
00:13:36,233 --> 00:13:38,600
（gt  global_energy_join  your_name  __tomm__
把your_name改成你的游戏id）

